OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1778605560
OL,3,CNew driving test booking rules come
OL,4,Cinto force - what has changed?
OL,6,FCan someone else still book a driving
OL,7,Ftest for you?
OL,9,FNo, it's now illegal. Under new laws,
OL,10,Fonly the learner taking the test can
OL,11,Fbook, change, cancel or swap a driving
OL,12,Ftest appointment.
OL,14,FDriving instructors are no longer
OL,15,Fallowed to do this on behalf of pupils.
OL,17,FWhat happens to tests already booked?
OL,19,FExisting bookings will still go ahead.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
